Governor of Georgia - Ballotpedia
snippet: Georgia has a Republican triplex. The Republican Party controls the offices of governor, secretary of state, and attorney general. See also: Georgia State Legislature, Georgia House of Representatives, Georgia State Senate ... The current Governor of Georgia is Brian Kemp (R).

title: 2026 Georgia gubernatorial election - Wikipedia
snippet: Republicans also control both the state senate and house of representatives, together with Kemp's governorship establishing a government trifecta, alongside complete Republican pick on the state's supreme court. A year prior to the elections, the 2025 Georgia Public Service Commission special election resulted in two Democrats being elected to the Commission.

title: Brian Kemp - Wikipedia
snippet: There was speculation that he would run in the 2026 United States Senate election in Georgia to challenge incumbent senator Jon Ossoff; in May 2025, he declined to run and endorsed Derek Dooley.

title: About Governor Brian P. Kemp | Governor Brian P. Kemp Office of the Governor
snippet: A native of Athens, Georgia, Brian Kemp started his first small business over 35 years ago with a pickup truck and a shovel. His experience as a small business owner has driven his mission to put hardworking Georgians first since taking office ...
